The paper deals with developing classification methods with high accuracy that also avoid unfair treatment of different groups, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which focuses on the development of algorithms and models for learning from data. The paper also incorporates fairness criteria into its worst-case logarithmic loss minimization, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with issues of fairness and discrimination, which could be classified under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on benchmark datasets, which could be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
